        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 12:31AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 1230 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
El Dorado, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Norphlet, Calion, Lisbon, Smackover, Kenova, El Dorado, and Lawson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
